The paper deals with the estimation of 3D parameters of lines from images, which is a common problem in robotics and computer vision. The use of a dynamical system and a nonlinear observer suggests that the paper belongs to the robotics sub-category (cs.RO). The paper also deals with image processing and computer vision techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the computer vision sub-category (cs.CV). The use of control applications and optimization techniques suggests that it could also belong to the systems and control sub-category (cs.SY). The use of nonlinear observers and control laws suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning sub-category (cs.LG) and the artificial intelligence sub-category (cs.AI).
